        "body": "Summary\n\n- Add Signal native exec/plugin approval capability gated by top-level approvals configuration.\n- Add thumbs-up / thumbs-down reaction approval handling for allow-once and deny, with explicit Signal approver auth.\n- Bind reactions only from native approval delivery, verify target-author identity, persist binding state, and re-check current approval route config before resolving.\n- Harden reaction bindings by normalizing Signal UUID author keys and removing timestamp-only cross-conversation fallback.\n\nVerification\n\n- [x] node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts\n- [x] pnpm check:changed\n- [x] git diff --check\n- [x] Manual dev.review loop passes addressed target route gating, target-author verification, generic send trust boundary, reaction hint binding, persisted route re-checks, and exact reaction binding scope.\n\nBehavior addressed: Signal can deliver approval prompts through native approval delivery and resolve authorized 👍 / 👎 reactions as allow-once / deny without cross-conversation timestamp fallback.\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts; pnpm check:changed; git diff --check\nEvidence after fix: focused Vitest passed 3 files / 24 tests; pnpm check:changed passed extension and extension-test lanes.\nObserved result after fix: Signal UUID author-key casing matches, reaction binding stays exact to the conversation/message key, and changed-lane typecheck/lint checks pass.\nWhat was not tested: live Signal transport/reaction roundtrip against a real Signal account in this fix pass.\n",
